{"TopicId":210754,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"(Regular) polygon shaped (procedural) tanks","CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-23T22:27:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-23T22:27:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n..why not? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E I think it\u0027s a game changer. Think of the incredibly creative sci-fi designs!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPS: Hmm, I wonder if this could be done with wings containing fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-11-23T22:31:32Z\u0022 title=\u002211/23/2022 10:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 23, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SkyFall2489","CreatedById":216984,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-23T23:58:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say some clipping, regular fuel tanks, and procedural wings would be functionally equivalent. (except for aerodynamics or performance)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-24T22:12:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022oleg-khvost-borg-cube-04.jpg?1544106333\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022800\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdnb.artstation.com/p/assets/images/images/014/476/191/small/oleg-khvost-borg-cube-04.jpg?1544106333\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022stardestroyers-e1579963906701.jpg?w=1024\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002240.63\u0022 height=\u0022416\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://sacredicon.files.wordpress.com/2020/01/stardestroyers-e1579963906701.jpg?w=1024\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI quite like the polyhedronal aesthetic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-11-24T22:13:45Z\u0022 title=\u002211/24/2022 10:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 24, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-24T23:04:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre fuel tanks going to be that procedural in KSP2? I thought it was going to be a set of fixed diameter tanks with a variety of fixed lengths that you can switch between to give the equivalent of e.g. the various FL-Tx00 tanks in a single part for convenience, much like structural tubes and engine plates in KSP. While I\u0027ve come around to the use of procedural parts in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E/RP-1, I don\u0027t like them for stock KSP as it\u0027s too much faff and to my knowledge that sort of millimetric-accurate part tweakery isn\u0027t coming to KSP2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}